ken peplowski quartet events at stanford ken peplowski quartet facebook twitter email print add to calendar ken peplowski's reputation as one of the greatest jazz clarinetists of the past 20 years is well deserved having had the great fortune just out of high school to play lead alto and solo clarinet in the tommy dorsey orchestra and later in benny goodman's last band he tempered his copious polka honed chops with a real big band era schooling though his name is synonymous with swing and he has frequently performed with howard alden dick hyman the late mel torme and many other modern swing artists his own recordings reveal a wider palette that includes classical pop and avant garde interests mel torme said there have been too few clarinetists to fill the void that benny goodman left ken peplowski is most certainly one of those few the man is magic when friday july 15 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where campbell recital hall 541 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $32 general $20 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27959 more info last modified july 11 2011
